The article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on December 31, 2020. The memorandum pertains to the construction and operation of border facilities associated with the international bridge project adjacent to the existing Pharr International Bridge. The memorandum outlines the conditions and requirements for the construction, operation, and maintenance of the border facilities. It specifies that the facilities shall be subject to all applicable laws and regulations and grants access to representatives of appropriate federal, state, and local agencies for inspection purposes. The memorandum also addresses the termination, revocation, or surrender of the permit, the rights of the United States to take possession of the facilities for national security reasons, and the transfer of ownership or control. It further discusses the responsibilities of the permittee regarding right-of-way grants, indemnification of the United States, and maintenance of the facilities. The memorandum concludes by stating that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.